===Etymology===
From a reduplication of {{m|en|ma}}; a trend present in many [[Indo-European]] languages, probably with ultimate origin in baby talk; or perhaps representing, in altered form, a continuation of {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|mome||mother, aunt|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*mōmǭ||mother, aunt}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*méh₂-méh₂}}, reduplication of {{m|ine-pro|*méh₂-||mother}}, related to {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Muhme||aunt|lang=de}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|mamma||mother, nurse|lang=la}}, {{etyl|ga|-}} {{term|mam||mother|lang=ga}}, {{etyl|lt|-}} {{term|mama|lang=lt}}, {{term|moma||mother|lang=lt}}.

